Crohn's Treatment:
A) < 20% low risk
older than > 30 yrs, small ileum disease, colon just apthomous ulcers - minimal sxs 
-don't need much tx, 9 mg - NO ASA/consider Sulfsalazine - Consider DIET even as tx
Consider RIS (Skyrizi) if fails
B) > 80% high risk
< 30 yrs, extensive involvement, perianal, DEEP ULCERS, stricture/penetrating/ho of surgery
START EARLY IFX, then UPA (Rinvoq)

